     <body>
     <div type="encomium">
   <head>In Authorem.</head>
   <lg>
      <l>I wish my rough-hewne lines might gratifie,</l>
      <l>The first borne of thy pleasing Poesie,</l>
      <l>These be but blossomes: what will be the fruite,</l>
      <l>When time and age, hath made thee more accute?</l>
      <l>Meane while how euer <hi>Momus</hi> bite the lippe,</l>
      <l>Each man will praise the weauers workmanship:</l>
      <l>When wittie verse is worthily regarded,</l>
      <l>Then shall thy verse be thankfully rewarded.</l>
   </lg>
   <closer>
      <signed>I. K. Mag: Art.</signed>
   </closer>
